{"_id":"MjNjOTkwZDcyZDUy","name":"Thug","permission":{"default":0},"type":"npc","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":15,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":2,"save":0},"dex":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"con":{"value":14,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":2,"save":0},"int":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"wis":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"cha":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0}},"attributes":{"ac":{"value":"11","min":0,"formula":"leather armor"},"hp":{"value":32,"min":0,"max":32,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":"5d8 + 10"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":0,"prof":0,"total":0},"spellcasting":"","speed":{"value":"30 ft","special":""},"prof":2,"spelldc":10,"spellLevel":0,"bar1":{"value":32,"min":0,"max":32},"bar2":{"value":11,"min":0,"max":0}},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div style=\"text-align: center\"><img src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/files.d20.io/images/27288847/j61j_MKX59mHMqyUp8yGbQ/med.png?1484250284\"></div><br>\n\n<strong>Thugs</strong> are ruthless enforcers skilled at intimidation  and violence. They work for money and have few  scruples.<br><br>\n\n<h2>Traits</h2><strong>Pack Tactics</strong>: The thug has advantage on an attack roll against a creature if at least one of the thug's allies is within 5 ft. of the creature and the ally isn't incapacitated.<br><br><h2>Actions</h2><strong>Multiattack</strong>: The thug makes two melee attacks.<br><br><strong>Mace</strong>: <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. <em>Hit:</em> 5 (1d6 + 2) bludgeoning damage.<br><br><strong>Heavy Crossbow</strong>: <em>Ranged Weapon Attack:</em> +2 to hit, range 100/400 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 5 (1d10) piercing damage.\n<hr><section class=\"secret\"><p><strong>GM Notes :</strong> </p><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-e32c5e8e-0207-576b-1623-63f8260db896\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Tashlyn offers affordable mercenaries, either <b>thugs </b>costing 2 sp per day each or veterans costing 2 gp per day each.</span></span></p><hr><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-e32c5e8e-0207-576b-1623-63f8260db896\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-dcb136be-0207-cd61-e42a-e17ac8aa2362\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Five Zhentarim<b> thugs</b> working for Urstul Floxin jumped both Floon and Renaer. They took them to a warehouse in the Dock Ward, so they could question Renaer—the son of Lord Dagult Neverember—about the whereabouts of the Stone of Golorr and his father's hidden cache of dragons. Before the interrogation could begin, members of the Xanathar Guild ambushed and killed the Zhent guards in the warehouse. The new arrivals mistook Floon for Renaer, knocked Floon unconscious, and dragged him away while Renaer hid and escaped their notice.</span></span></span></span></p><hr><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-e32c5e8e-0207-576b-1623-63f8260db896\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-dcb136be-0207-cd61-e42a-e17ac8aa2362\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">The characters <span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-56984f75-0208-56bf-875d-8965cbe949f2\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">can confront Esloon Bezant (LE male Thayan human mage) and his gang of five<b> thugs </b>and either defeat them or bribe them with at least 500 gp.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><hr><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-60ac86eb-0208-d2b7-b376-a7d967510cfd\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">In the 2nd level Order of the Gauntlet mission, the characters must visit the Field Ward and, as a fight threatens to break out, make three successful DC 12 Charisma (Intimidation) checks before failing three checks, or else defeat four <b>thugs</b> (preferably without killing them) to disperse the would-be brawlers.</span></span></p><hr><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-60ac86eb-0208-d2b7-b376-a7d967510cfd\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-6d903f1a-0209-64d3-fa40-a177aacf674c\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">The floor of area G8 is strewn with bodies. Two <b>thugs </b>holding bloody maces stand over them.</span></span></span></span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Four veterans of House Gralhund (each with 30 hit points remaining) are fighting off an attacking force of Zhents consisting of three <b>thugs </b>(each with 20 hit points remaining). The Zhents are trying to get to area G16, but the guards are blocking them.<br><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">\nIf the characters do nothing to affect the outcome of this fight, assume that it ends with three House Gralhund veterans still alive and all the Zhents dead.</span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-6d10275f-020a-0b3a-a5b2-d5ab25715d21\"></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">If the characters come to Grinda's defense, Noska Ur'gray orders his <b>thugs </b>to attack them while he takes potshots at the characters with his crossbow. Two rounds later, eight more bandits leap down from the Kraken's Folly (area D1) and join the fray. These hooligans were paid 1 gp each to watch Noska's back. The characters can turn them against Noska by offering a larger bribe (at least 5 gp each).</span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-175c33e5-020a-7f10-d4f2-5fb920d63cdb\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">As the characters leave the Fuoco residence, with or without Agorn as their prisoner, they are surrounded by nine Zhentarim<b> thugs</b>. The thugs fight to the death while Agorn tries to escape. If he gets away, the characters might encounter him again.</span></span></span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-175c33e5-020a-7f10-d4f2-5fb920d63cdb\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-c1b723ec-020a-d724-4f39-8214c4d078cf\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">If Manshoon is the main villain, he sends his simulacrum along with Agorn Fuoco (NE male Turami human bard), Vevette Blackwater (CE female Tethyrian human swashbuckler), and three Zhent <b>thugs</b> when the characters leave the vault. If Agorn and Vevette were killed or otherwise disposed of earlier, replace each of them with one additional thug.</span></span></span></span></span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-175c33e5-020a-7f10-d4f2-5fb920d63cdb\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-c1b723ec-020a-d724-4f39-8214c4d078cf\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-797c2561-020c-6c77-f44c-b3e9f4b86d75\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Emmek Frewn (see Business Rival) needs 1,500 gp to pay off a loan with interest. If he doesn't repay the coin in a tenday, Istrid Horn sends Zhentarim<b> thugs</b> to threaten, if not hurt, him. Emmek comes to the characters with hat in hand, preying on their generosity while denying any wrongdoing on his part.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-175c33e5-020a-7f10-d4f2-5fb920d63cdb\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-c1b723ec-020a-d724-4f39-8214c4d078cf\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-797c2561-020c-6c77-f44c-b3e9f4b86d75\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-a8bc677a-020c-d61e-e164-680ac2d5721c\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">The card players are Sidra Romeir (LE female Calishite human veteran) and two subordinates (LE male Tethyrian human <b>thugs</b>). Since the force field around Kolat Towers keeps out riffraff, Sidra assumes the characters are guests of Manshoon arriving for a clandestine meeting. If the characters give her no reason to believe otherwise, she and her thugs escort them wherever they ask to go. If it becomes clear that the characters don't belong in the towers, Sidra and her thugs attack. Combat in this area draws the attention of Manafret Cherryport in area K3, who investigates.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Four Zhent <b>thugs</b> relax in area K14—one trying to rest, two others playing cards, and the fourth sitting on the edge of a bed, re-stringing a heavy crossbow.<br><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">\nThe thugs work for Manshoon and leap up to attack anyone they don't recognize as one of their own. A successful DC 17 Charisma (Deception) check convinces these Zhents that the characters are their allies.</span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-40b5ef26-020d-8ea9-1f5e-c7aad80b7995\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Corylus Thann, a racist Waterdavian noble, is paying the Zhentarim not to reveal that he hired Zhent <b>thugs</b> to assault nonhumans.</span></span></span></p></section>","public":""},"alignment":"Any Non-good Alignment","race":"","type":"humanoid (any race)","environment":"","cr":0.5,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":100},"source":"Roll 20","class":""},"traits":{"size":"med","di":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":[],"custom":""},"senses":"passive Perception 10","languages":{"value":[],"custom":""}},"currency":{"pp":0,"gp":0,"ep":0,"sp":0,"cp":0},"skills":{"acr":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"ani":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"arc":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"ath":{"value":0,"ability":"str","bonus":0,"mod":2,"passive":12},"dec":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"his":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"ins":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"itm":{"value":1,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":2,"passive":12},"inv":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"med":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"nat":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"prc":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"prf":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"per":{"value":0,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"rel":{"value":0,"ability":"int","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"slt":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"ste":{"value":0,"ability":"dex","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10},"sur":{"value":0,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":0,"passive":10}},"spells":{"spell1":{"value":0,"max":0,"override":null},"spell2":{"value":0,"max":0,"override":null},"spell3":{"value":0,"m