{"_id":"MjQ0NjQxNWYxZTQ1","name":"Cultist","permission":{"default":0},"type":"npc","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"dex":{"value":12,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":1,"save":0},"con":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"int":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"wis":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"cha":{"value":10,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0}},"attributes":{"ac":{"value":"12","min":0,"formula":"leather armor"},"hp":{"value":9,"min":0,"max":9,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":"2d8"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":1,"prof":0,"total":1},"spellcasting":"","speed":{"value":"30 ft","special":""},"prof":2,"spelldc":10,"spellLevel":0,"bar1":{"value":9,"min":0,"max":9},"bar2":{"value":12,"min":0,"max":0}},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<strong>Cultists</strong> swear allegiance to dark powers such as  elemental princes, demon lords, or archdevils. Most  conceal their loyalties to avoid being ostracized,  imprisoned, or executed for their beliefs. Unlike evil acolytes, cultists often show signs of insanity in their  beliefs and practices.<br><br>\n\n<h2>Traits</h2><strong>Dark Devotion</strong>: The cultist has advantage on saving throws against being charmed or frightened.<br><br><h2>Actions</h2><strong>Scimitar</strong>: <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. <em>Hit:</em> 4 (1d6 + 1) slashing damage.\n<hr><section class=\"secret\"><p><strong>GM Notes :</strong> </p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">The survivor is Vaelle Lurval (LE female Tethyrian human <b>cultist</b>), a 30-year-old Waterdavian florist. She was brought into the cult by her boyfriend, Holiver Tornrudder, who lies dead nearby. The other dead cultist is named Kaeth Warloon.<br><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">If she is healed, Vaelle regains consciousness. She reveals that the cult fanatics, Arn Xalrondar and Seffia Naelryke, would likely have taken the stone to an old windmill in the Southern Ward, where they hold their own ceremonies worshiping Asmodeus. Vaelle can provide directions, or she can lead characters there if she is healed fully, for the sake of avenging her murdered lover.<br></span><br>Vaelle believes that the cult fanatics acted on their own, not under Lord Cassalanter's orders. She won't reveal the Cassalanters as the leaders of the cult unless magically compelled to do so.</p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-02cb1765-fd40-12b7-5b70-c0843ac46277\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">If the Cassalanters are the villains, they send three cult fanatics and three <b>cultists</b> as the characters are leaving the vault. Victoro's doppelganger manservant, Willifort Crowelle, leads the group in his tiefling guise unless the characters killed him or otherwise disposed of him earlier.</span></span></span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-02cb1765-fd40-12b7-5b70-c0843ac46277\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-65ec846f-fd40-6805-54dc-bbdb04501b78\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Tired <b>cultists</b> sleep in area A5 after ceremonies, particularly if they drank too much wine.<br><br>\n\n</span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">An hour before a cult gathering, five human <b>cultists</b> are in area A6 donning their regalia.</span></p><hr><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">Three human<b> cultists </b>wearing red robes, devil masks, and wooden holy symbols of Asmodeus kneel before the statue in area A7, feverishly chanting an infernal hymn. (During a cult gathering, the number of cultists present increases dramatically.)<br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><br>\n\n</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38 ; margin-top: 0pt ; margin-bottom: 0pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-d3fa2a9e-fd41-3135-d56a-05afbe77b6bb\"></span></span><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-2285dac4-fd41-7ab0-9e87-5f91cd10f550\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">If the cult is here in force, thirty human cultists stand in neat rows before the statue, chanting to Asmodeus with wooden goblets in hand while their leader, Victoro Cassalanter, tosses offerings into the bowl. Roughly half of the cultists are members of the nobility; the rest are Waterdavian rabble brought into the cult to fill out the ranks. Standing around the perimeter are Willifort Crowelle, Tissina Khyret, Laiba Rosse, and Jandar Chergoba (see Head Servants). Their job is to make sure the other cultists behave themselves while Ammalia Cassalanter walks gracefully through the crowd with a golden decanter, ceremonially pouring wine into the cultists' goblets for toasting to the Lord of the Nine Hells. Lady Cassalanter's six imps (see area C25) are perched invisibly on the statue.</span></span><br></span></p></section>","public":""},"alignment":"Any Non-good Alignment","race":"","type":"humanoid (any race)","environment":"","cr":0.125,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":25},"source":"Roll 20","class":""},"traits":{"size":"med","di":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"custom":""},"ci":