{"_id":"NzZkZDY3NjhkMmE3","name":"Magister Umbero Zastro","permission":{"default":0},"type":"npc","data":{"abilities":{"str":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"dex":{"value":12,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":1,"save":0},"con":{"value":11,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":0,"save":0},"int":{"value":12,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":1,"save":0},"wis":{"value":14,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":2,"save":0},"cha":{"value":16,"proficient":0,"min":3,"mod":3,"save":0}},"attributes":{"ac":{"value":"11","min":0,"formula":""},"hp":{"value":9,"min":0,"max":9,"temp":0,"tempmax":0,"formula":"2d8"},"init":{"value":0,"bonus":0,"mod":1,"prof":0,"total":1},"spellcasting":"","speed":{"value":"30 ft","special":""},"prof":1,"spelldc":10,"spellLevel":0,"bar1":{"value":9,"min":0,"max":9},"bar2":{"value":11,"min":0,"max":0}},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>Nobles</strong> wield great authority and influence as  members of the upper class, possessing wealth and  connections that can make them as powerful as  monarchs and generals. A noble often travels in the  company of guards, as well as servants who are  commoners.<br></div><br>\n\nThe noble’s statistics can also be used to represent  <strong>courtiers</strong> who aren’t of noble birth.<br><br>\n\n<h2>Actions</h2>\n\n<strong>Rapier</strong>: <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 5 (1d8 + 1) piercing damage.<br><br>\n\n<h2>Reactions</h2>\n\n<strong>Parry</strong>: The noble adds 2 to its AC against one melee attack that would hit it. To do so, the noble must see the attacker and be wielding a melee weapon.\n<hr><section class=\"secret\"><p><strong>GM Notes :</strong> </p><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-5b915e92-e7a4-c92d-f868-82e552539db9\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">The presiding magister is <b>Umbero Zastro</b>, a handsome, eloquent, and fair-minded half-elf in his thirties. He's known for his finely honed sense of poetic justice and for meting out unconventional punishments.</span></span></p><p><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-5b915e92-e7a4-c92d-f868-82e552539db9\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\"><span id=\"userscript-docs-internal-guid-11a6af66-e7a5-35c2-b8ff-dc41bb1a505c\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline\">The magister has already heard the testimony of the arresting officers, as well as that of any eyewitnesses. The characters are given an hour to plead their case while he asks questions. A character who tries to deceive Zastro must make a Charisma (Deception) check contested by the magister's Wisdom (Insight) check. A character who loses this contest is found guilty of hampering justice, locked up for a tenday, and fined 200 gp, on top of any other punishments meted out for crimes committed against the city and its citizenry. Those who can't or won't pay the fine are sentenced to hard labor for a year in Amendsfarm, a City Guard-run labor camp among the farms of Undercliff.</span></span></span></span><br></p></section>","public":""},"alignment":"Lawful Neutral","race":"","type":"humanoid (half-elf)","environment":"","cr":0,"spellLevel":0,"xp":{"value":0},"source":"Roll 20","class":""},"traits":{"size":"med","di":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dr":{"value":[],"custom":""},"dv":{"value":[],"custom":""},"ci":{"value":[],"custom":""},"senses":"darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 12","languages":{"value":["common","elvish"],"custom":""}},"currency":{"pp":0,"gp":0,"ep":0,"sp":0,"cp":0},"skills":{"acr":{"value":0.5,"ability":"dex","bonus":-0.5,"mod":1,"passive":11},"ani":{"value":0.5,"ability":"wis","bonus":-0.5,"mod":2,"passive":12},"arc":{"value":0.5,"ability":"int","bonus":-0.5,"mod":1,"passive":11},"ath":{"value":0.5,"ability":"str","bonus":-0.5,"mod":0,"passive":10},"dec":{"value":2,"ability":"cha","bonus":0,"mod":5,"passive":15},"his":{"value":0.5,"ability":"int","bonus":-0.5,"mod":1,"passive":11},"ins":{"value":2,"ability":"wis","bonus":0,"mod":4,"passive"